Georgia Power Ga . nuke at 23 pct power - NRC . Georgia Power Co ' s 1 , 162 megawatt ( MW ) Vogtle 2 nuclear power unit , which was manually shut late Monday , has restarted and is at 23 percent power , the Nuclear Regulatory Commission said Wednesday . The company earlier said the unit located in Waynesboro , Ga . , was shut due to a malfunctioning feedwater regulator valve . At 0916 EDT , a company spokeswoman said the unit had reached 35 percent power and should resume full power by week ' s end . Georgia Power ' s other Vogtle unit , with an identical generating capacity , is operating at full power . Georgia Power is a unit of Southern Co . - - New York Power Desk + 212 - 859 - 1628 
